{"@type":"Question","name":"Can my spouse file bankruptcy without me?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes in every state, but the consequences differ. In common-law states, your spouse's individual filing affects only their solely-owned debts and assets. In community-property states (AZ, CA, ID, LA, NM, NV, TX, WA, WI), community debts can be discharged even though only one spouse files, and the trustee can reach community property to satisfy those debts - which means individual filing in a community-property state is effectively a household-level event."}},
