{"@type":"Question","name":"Should we file jointly or individually?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Joint filing saves one set of attorney fees and one filing fee, doubles some exemptions (federal and some state), and discharges both spouses' debts in one case. Individual filing makes sense when only one spouse has dischargeable debt, when filing timing differs (one spouse needs to wait out the 1328(f) bar), or when one spouse has non-exempt assets the other does not want at risk."}},
